<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn148">  148  Joyce is alluding to the British soldiers firing into the crowds at Croke Park in Dublin on &lsquo;Bloody Sunday,&rsquo; 21 November 1920, a brutal senseless reaction to the assassination, by Michael Collins' rebels, of British spies on the morning of the same day.  </div>
